<div id="review_949500864" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/949500864" />
    <a title="Czarny Pies" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies"><img alt="Czarny Pies" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400687408p2/29160274.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/949500864?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Czarny Pies" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Czarny Pies" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies">Czarny Pies</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">History Students and Buffs</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Czarny by: </span>
      I am an Orwell Fan
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29160274-czarny-pies?shelf=political-theory">political-theory</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer949500864" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7913821277769995039">This book has tremendous value has an historical document in that it is an extremely well documented book about the squalid living conditions of the British Working Class before the advent of the modern welfare state. It does not describe today&apos;s world and hence no longer relates to current political issues.<br/><br/>Nonetheless, Wigan Pier describes very brilliantly what was. It thus provides a good part of the explanation why intellectuals and middle class people were so attracted Socialism during the i</span>
  <span id="freeText7913821277769995039" style="display:none">This book has tremendous value has an historical document in that it is an extremely well documented book about the squalid living conditions of the British Working Class before the advent of the modern welfare state. It does not describe today's world and hence no longer relates to current political issues.<br /><br />Nonetheless, Wigan Pier describes very brilliantly what was. It thus provides a good part of the explanation why intellectuals and middle class people were so attracted Socialism during the inter-war years.<br /><br />There was a conspiracy of silence amongst the communists and fellow travellers in the 1930s that kept the general public unaware of the Ukrainian famine, the Gulags and the Great Terror of Stalinist Russia because they were so afraid that by criticizing Communism which represented hope, human society would not be able to solve the prevalent problems in society as described so brilliantly by Orwell.<br /><br />The same year that Orwell published this book he would leave for Spain to fight against Fascism. The experience cured him of his illusions about communism. It did not however reduce his concern for the poor and underprivileged in our society. Wigan Pier is a great book written by a great man.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7913821277769995039" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


